solution_summary: The function days_in_this_month() first gets the current date using datetime.date.today(). Then it calculates the first day of the next month by adding 32 days to the current date (since the current date is guaranteed to be within the current month). The last day of the current month is then calculated by subtracting one day from the first day of the next month. Finally, the day of the last day of the month is returned as the solution.
